through that hole in the wall.

12:48.944 --> 12:50.544
The door?

12:50.612 --> 12:53.313
Maybe we should get
a suite here for them, okay?

12:53.365 --> 12:55.216
Ben Wyatt!
Hello!

12:55.283 --> 12:56.650
Uh, hi, Leslie.

12:56.701 --> 12:58.152
- Good to see you.
- You too.

12:58.220 --> 13:00.504
Wow, you're really burning up.

13:00.589 --> 13:01.705
Can I get some money

13:01.790 --> 13:03.541
for the cab that I took
over here, please?

13:03.625 --> 13:04.558
Sure.
How much?

13:04.626 --> 13:05.559
I'm not sure.

13:05.627 --> 13:06.760
I looked at the meter,

13:06.828 --> 13:09.179
and it had
Egyptian hieroglyphics on it.

13:09.264 --> 13:10.831
- Wow.
- Do you know the exchange rate?

13:10.882 --> 13:12.716
So should we do this?

13:12.801 --> 13:15.035
Oh, boy.
Hold on.

13:15.103 --> 13:16.837
- Be careful.
- What?

13:16.905 --> 13:20.341
The floor and the wall
just switched.

13:20.408 --> 13:21.775
Okay.

13:21.843 --> 13:23.978
Walk very carefully.

13:31.958 --> 13:33.500
You know, I find it a little insulting

13:33.620 --> 13:34.954
that you don't trust me
to handle this.

13:35.005 --> 13:37.290
It's not that
I don't trust you, okay?

13:37.358 --> 13:40.059
It's just... This harvest festival
is my project.

13:40.127 --> 13:42.195
It's my career on the line.

13:42.263 --> 13:43.396
And I just need to make sure

13:43.464 --> 13:46.833
that I've done everything I can
to make it work.

13:46.901 --> 13:48.651
Okay.

13:48.736 --> 13:50.170
It's showtime.

13:50.237 --> 13:51.771
Okay.

13:51.822 --> 13:53.940
Good evening, everyone.
I'm Leslie Monster.

13:53.991 --> 13:55.775
And this is <i>Nightline.</i>

13:55.826 --> 13:57.160
Okay, I wouldn't open
with that.

13:57.244 --> 13:58.328
No?

13:58.412 --> 14:00.180
- Why don't we sit down. Okay?
- Yep.

14:00.247 --> 14:04.050
Libertarianism is all
about individual liberty,

14:04.118 --> 14:05.451
and it should never be defined

14:05.519 --> 14:07.837
by the terms "liberal"
or "conservative."

14:07.922 --> 14:10.540
And communism is
no good, right?

14:10.624 --> 14:11.541
That's right.

14:11.625 --> 14:13.359
Big swing and a miss.

14:13.427 --> 14:14.494
And what's the word

14:14.562 --> 14:17.030
for when a few clerics are
in charge?

14:17.097 --> 14:18.064
Religious oligarchy.

14:18.132 --> 14:20.466
Holy [bleep].

14:20.518 --> 14:22.852
- I can remember things.
- I guess.

14:22.937 --> 14:25.405
Mm, hey, keep mine rare.

14:25.472 --> 14:28.558
A man after my own heart.

14:30.377 --> 14:33.413
I vomited
somewhere in this room.

14:33.480 --> 14:35.882
I don't remember where, though.

14:35.950 --> 14:39.586
Wait. You might want to check
that drawer.

14:39.653 --> 14:42.422
Stop...

14:42.489 --> 14:43.890
Pooping.

14:43.958 --> 14:46.059
You have to get up
off the floor now.

14:46.126 --> 14:47.427
This floor is my friend.

14:47.494 --> 14:49.996
Nothing like a complete
physical breakdown

14:50.064 --> 14:52.799
to make a guy seem
less intimidating.

14:52.867 --> 14:54.434
I love the flu.

14:54.501 --> 14:55.919
And then I said,
"uh, you know what?

14:56.003 --> 15:00.340
I think we need to get
these bananas out of here."

15:00.407 --> 15:01.641
Have a seat, boys.

15:01.709 --> 15:03.610
Oh, hey, Tom,
glad you could make it.

15:03.677 --> 15:06.045
Uh, you have a nice day
with your spa buddies?

15:06.113 --> 15:07.730
Actually, yes, Ben, I did.

15:07.815 --> 15:09.415
And my spa buddies own

15:09.483 --> 15:11.234
a couple of car dealerships
in town,

15:11.318 --> 15:12.886
and they've agreed to donate

15:12.953 --> 15:15.255
a fleet of vehicles
for harvest festival...

15:15.322 --> 15:18.124
25 vans for the entire event.

15:18.192 --> 15:20.460
Okay, Tom, I'm ready.
Get up there and introduce me.

15:20.527 --> 15:21.828
You got it.

15:21.895 --> 15:23.663
I can't let you
do this, Leslie.

15:23.731 --> 15:26.699
Hey, this ain't
your call, McCluskey.

15:26.767 --> 15:30.086
Hey, Ron,
can I ask you a question?

15:30.170 --> 15:33.106
- Sure.
- It's about April.

15:33.173 --> 15:36.409
I don't like to get involved
in people's personal...

15:36.477 --> 15:39.629
I hurt her feelings,
and now she's pissed at me.

15:39.713 --> 15:41.247
I feel like
if I could just explain myself,

15:41.298 --> 15:44.250
she'd understand,
but she's avoiding me.

15:44.318 --> 15:46.486
It's making me miserable.

15:49.456 --> 15:52.091
April's in the hospital,
sick with the flu.

15:52.142 --> 15:53.109
What?

15:53.193 --> 15:54.560
I knew it!

15:54.612 --> 15:55.778
I didn't know that.

15:55.863 --> 15:57.730
- Is she okay?
- Yeah, she's fine.

15:57.781 --> 15:59.565
You can go visit her
tomorrow morning.

15:59.633 --> 16:01.117
But don't tell her I told you.

16:01.201 --> 16:03.503
I won't.

16:03.570 --> 16:06.272
No, no.
Nope.

16:06.323 --> 16:07.273
Come here.
Ugh.

16:07.324 --> 16:08.992
Ohhh!

16:09.076 --> 16:12.445
Before we get started,
a quick announcement...

16:12.513 --> 16:15.348
Every Thursday night
is ladies' night

16:15.416 --> 16:18.751
down at the Snakehole Lounge
over on Burnham Avenue.

16:18.819 --> 16:21.254
Ladies get two drinks
for the price of one.

16:21.305 --> 16:22.822
Oh, no, that can't be right.

16:22.890 --> 16:25.425
That's way too good of a deal.

16:25.476 --> 16:27.126
Nope.

16:27.194 --> 16:29.178
That is what it says.

16:29.263 --> 16:30.179
Wow.

16:30.264 --> 16:31.648
That sounds like a fun time.

16:31.732 --> 16:33.700
Anyway, uh,

16:33.767 --> 16:35.401
it is now my great honor
to welcome to the stage

16:35.469 --> 16:38.371
the woman responsible
for the entire harvest festival.

16:38.439 --> 16:40.473
Ladies and gentlemen,
Leslie Knope!

16:53.454 --> 16:54.820
Every one of you,

16:54.872 --> 16:57.206
just by showing
up here tonight,

16:57.291 --> 16:58.624
has already made history.

16:58.676 --> 17:01.527
In days past,
the harvest festival

17:01.595 --> 17:03.212
was the cornerstone

17:03.297 --> 17:05.848
of Pawnee's
small-business community...

17:05.933 --> 17:07.467
a weeklong showcase

17:07.518 --> 17:10.803
for everything from textiles
to small farms.

17:10.854 --> 17:13.021
By our estimates,
as many as 30,000 people

17:13.107 --> 17:14.674
might attend the festival,

17:14.742 --> 17:16.075
and the monetary value

17:16.143 --> 17:18.560
of that kind of direct
customer-to-business exposure

17:18.645 --> 17:21.013
is, frankly, incalculable.

17:23.200 --> 17:25.218
What?

17:25.285 --> 17:26.752
Three, two, one.

17:26.819 --> 17:28.204
And my shift's over.

17:28.288 --> 17:30.189
What the [bleep]
is your problem?

17:30.257 --> 17:31.858
Whoa, I thought
you weren't gonna lose it.

17:31.925 --> 17:33.993
While I was on duty, I didn't.
Now it's just me.

17:34.061 --> 17:36.429
I get that you're mad
that I kissed Andy, okay?

17:36.497 --> 17:37.830
But it was a moment
of confusion,

17:37.898 --> 17:39.198
and it was a mistake.

17:39.249 --> 17:40.700
And I'm very sorry.

17:40.768 --> 17:42.085
You want to hate me forever?

17:42.169 --> 17:43.553
- Okay.
- Fine!

17:43.637 --> 17:44.937
You know what?
I don't care.

17:45.005 --> 17:46.372
But you shouldn't take it out
on Andy,

17:46.440 --> 17:48.874
because he really likes you,
and he did nothing wrong.

17:48.926 --> 17:52.211
And just for the record,
I'm starting to hate you too.

17:54.948 --> 17:57.683
That's the most
I've ever liked Ann.

17:57.735 --> 17:59.769
The time is now.

17:59.853 --> 18:01.904
The place is Pawnee.

18:01.989 --> 18:04.223
Let's make history.

18:06.160 --> 18:08.745
That was amazing.

18:08.829 --> 18:10.396
That was a flu-ridden
Michael Jordan

18:10.464 --> 18:12.598
at the '97 NBA finals.

18:12.666 --> 18:14.233
That was...

18:14.284 --> 18:16.035
Kirk Gibson
hobbling up to the plate

18:16.103 --> 18:17.587
and hitting a homer
off of Dennis Eckersley.

18:17.671 --> 18:20.740
That was...

18:20.808 --> 18:23.476
That was Leslie Knope.

18:23.544 --> 18:25.745
Thank you so much.
Any questions?

18:25.813 --> 18:27.463
Yes, sir?

18:27.548 --> 18:30.149
Are we going to get
the same sales-tax incentives

18:30.217 --> 18:31.267
we used to?

18:31.351 --> 18:33.186
That's a very good
question, sir,

18:33.253 --> 18:36.255
and I would counter
with my own question, which is,

18:36.306 --> 18:38.808
why is half of your face
all swirly?

18:38.892 --> 18:40.293
Okay, um, unfortunately,

18:40.360 --> 18:43.312
Leslie has another very
important meeting right now.

18:43.397 --> 18:44.814
So if you have
any other questions,

18:44.898 --> 18:46.599
you can just direct them,
uh, towards me.

18:46.667 --> 18:47.817
Give it up, everybody,

18:47.901 --> 18:49.602
for Scott Bakula
from <i>Quantum Leap.</i>

18:49.653 --> 18:52.038
All right.
Okay, let's...

18:52.105 --> 18:53.906
Excuse me.

18:53.957 --> 18:56.509
Um, and to answer
your question, sir,

18:56.577 --> 18:58.411
there will be
sales-tax incentives this year.

18:58.479 --> 18:59.912
I think I should drive you
to the hospital.

18:59.980 --> 19:01.581
Was I wearing a tiara
when I came in here?

19:01.648 --> 19:03.116
Because if you happen upon it,

19:03.183 --> 19:04.717
will you have Lady Pennyface
retrieve it

19:04.785 --> 19:06.119
and send it posthence?

19:06.186 --> 19:07.220
Chocolate-covered popcorn.

19:09.956 --> 19:11.974
- Oh, hey.
- Hey, there.

19:12.059 --> 19:14.227
I got you, uh,
some waffles here,

19:14.294 --> 19:16.095
courtesy of JJ's diner,

19:16.146 --> 19:17.897
and chicken soup,
courtesy of me.

19:17.964 --> 19:19.816
- I'll take the waffles.
- Okay.

19:19.900 --> 19:22.235
Thank you.

19:22.302 --> 19:23.903
So how did the rest
of the meeting go?

19:23.970 --> 19:26.823
Um, well, you said you needed

19:26.907 --> 19:28.474
80 total businesses
to participate.

19:28.525 --> 19:30.076
Yeah.

19:30.143 --> 19:31.244
We have 110...

19:31.311 --> 19:32.612
And counting.

19:32.663 --> 19:34.980
So, uh, nice work, Leslie.

19:35.032 --> 19:36.999
- Nice work to you too.
- Oh.

19:37.084 --> 19:39.285
Uh, left the chicken soup there,
just in case.

19:39.336 --> 19:41.537
It's an old family recipe.

19:41.622 --> 19:44.123
It's not a big deal, but...

19:44.174 --> 19:46.292
- Thank you for that.
- Okay.

19:50.848 --> 19:52.164
Hi, April.

19:52.216 --> 19:54.050
It's me, Andy.

19:54.134 --> 19:56.519
Just stay sleeping.

19:56.603 --> 20:00.339
I am going to be here
when you wake up.

20:00.407 --> 20:02.441
I will not leave your side.

20:07.347 --> 20:11.734
You could be asleep for hours.
Maybe I'll come back later.

20:11.818 --> 20:14.019
Hope you feel better.
Okay.

20:14.071 --> 20:16.455
Oh, and I know you think
that I'm a jerk,

20:16.523 --> 20:19.158
but I hope you can forgive me.

20:22.746 --> 20:24.463
Gross.
Your forehead is all sweaty.

20:24.531 --> 20:26.048
That's gross.

20:28.135 --> 20:29.969
But I still like you.

20:30.036 --> 20:31.037
Okay.

20:31.104 --> 20:33.038
Oh, that's disgusting.

20:40.557 --> 20:41.674
Got your message.
What's up?

20:41.758 --> 20:43.476
I got a call
from the boys upstairs.

20:44.064 --> 20:45.726
And they have
a new assignment for us.

20:45.846 --> 20:46.890
- Okay.
- Yeah.

20:47.010 --> 20:50.387
And I feel like we should ask
for an extension to stay here.

20:50.706 --> 20:52.087
Yes, definitely.
You know...

20:52.207 --> 20:54.092
The festival thing's
getting pretty huge,

20:54.120 --> 20:56.717
and, uh, couple loose ends
that need tying up.

20:56.837 --> 20:59.077
Good, so I'll make the call,
then, to get the extension?

20:59.123 --> 21:00.580
- Yeah, they need our help.
- For the loose ends.

21:00.700 --> 21:01.644
- Great.
- Good.

21:01.695 --> 21:03.556
Okay, you need
a ride back to the office?

21:03.607 --> 21:05.576
No, no, I'm gonna go
for a light 15k.

21:05.696 --> 21:06.653
I missed yesterday.

21:08.121 --> 21:09.475
Way to go, buddy.
Way to go.

